  "text": "Researchers are currently uncovering rich connections between graphs, information ¤ow, and formation control [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . Local restrictions on communication may induce arbitrary switching in the network. In light of this, Ji and Egerstedt [CITATION_4] design graph-based controllers that maintain connectivity as robots rendezvous. Jadbabaie et al. [CITATION_5] approach the issue differently, constructing controllers that are stable under arbitrary switching sequences.",
